---
const rawBase = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = rawBase.endsWith('/') ? rawBase : rawBase + '/';
---

<section class="demo">
  <div class="section-shell demo-inner">
    <div class="demo-copy reveal">
      <p class="section-kicker">Built for real handoffs</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">This is a live project session, not a laggy screen share.</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        Shadow syncs the filesystem itself. Hosts stay in their editor. Joiners stay in theirs.
        The demo below is the actual product rhythm you want people to imagine from a launch post.
      </p>

      <div class="demo-notes">
        <article>
          <span>Starts fast</span>
          <p>One install command, then `shadow start .` or the VS Code sidebar.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Shares cleanly</span>
          <p>The copied join command is the handoff, so nobody has to manually reconstruct the long URL.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Stays private</span>
          <p>The E2E key stays in the URL fragment, which never gets sent to the relay.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-stage reveal r-d1" data-demo-root>
      <div class="demo-window">
        <div class="window-chrome">
          <div class="chrome-dots">
            <i></i><i></i><i></i>
          </div>
          <span class="chrome-title">shadow walkthrough</span>
          <div class="chrome-space"></div>
        </div>
        <video
          src={`${base}demo.mp4`}
          autoplay
          loop
          muted
          playsinline
          preload="metadata"
          data-demo-video
        ></video>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-footer">
        <button
          type="button"
          class="ghost-button"
          data-demo-toggle
          data-demo-source="demo_section"
          data-demo-state="playing"
        >
          <span data-demo-label>Pause loop</span>
        </button>
        <p>Keep this handy for launch replies. It shows the product in one glance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .demo {
    margin-bottom: var(--gap);
  }

  .demo-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .demo-window {
    background: var(--surface);
    border-radius: 1.6rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
  }

  .window-chrome {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.95rem 1.1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }

  .chrome-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .chrome-dots i {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .chrome-dots i:nth-child(1) { background: #ff5f57; }
  .chrome-dots i:nth-child(2) { background: #febc2e; }
  .chrome-dots i:nth-child(3) { background: #28c840; }

  .chrome-title {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .chrome-space { width: 46px; }

  video {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .demo-notes {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .demo-notes article,
  .demo-footer {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 1.2rem;
    background: var(--paper);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  }

  .demo-notes article {
    padding: 1rem 1.05rem;
  }

  .demo-notes span {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.32rem;
  }

  .demo-notes p,
  .demo-footer p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .demo-footer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .demo-footer p {
    max-width: 22rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .demo-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .demo-footer {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }
  }
</style>
